Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Theaidetos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.15978. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0911)
